[resource]
script = ExtResource("1_wchga")
ref_name = "NIRCam"
ref_desc = "[b][color=light_blue]Section:[/color] 4.4[/b]
The Near Infra-Red Camera is the main imaging devince, but can also do some of the basic functions of other instruments. 
It uses a dichroic beam splitter to split incoming light into two beams, depending on their wavelength. For the smaller wavelenght it uses 8 smaller sensors setup in two grids of4, while the longer wave lenghts get captured on 2 sensors, each the size of one group of smaller sensors."
wavelength_low = 600.0
wavelength_high = 5000.0
metadata/_custom_type_script = "uid://chyrk1ts4wb7h"
